    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix MAC verification failure in Security Mode Command handling\n\n### Summary\nThe `handle_security_mode_command()` function in the NR UE NAS module was failing to properly verify the MAC in Security Mode Command messages from the network. This caused the UE to reject valid security mode commands, preventing successful registration.\n\nRoot cause was missing NAS sequence number synchronization before MAC computation. The function also had a missing return statement that could cause execution to continue after error conditions.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/NR_UE/nr_nas_msg.c`: Added NAS sequence number synchronization in `handle_security_mode_command()` \n- `openair3/NAS/NR_UE/nr_nas_msg.c`: Added missing return statement after PDU length check\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure OAI UE to connect to a 5G core network\n2. Observe registration failure during security mode command exchange\n3. Check NAS logs showing \"MAC does not match\" errors\n4. UE sends Security Mode Reject instead of Security Mode Complete\n\nThe fix ensures proper sequence number handling and prevents invalid memory access, allowing successful security context establishment.\n"
}